&lt;p&gt;TextUs is the leading performance messaging platform for engaging customers and workers. We improve business outcomes by allowing users to deliver messages over high performance texting channels optimized through superior analytics, native AI features, and seamless integration with systems of record.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Senior Product Manager at TextUs, you&#39;ll own what we build and why — driving discovery, shaping the roadmap, and authoring the Product Briefs our development process runs on. You&#39;ll work with a dedicated product team spanning product ownership, product marketing, and product design to take your briefs from problem definition through launch, with a direct hand in how TextUs differentiates, including AI-based capabilities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CORE RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discovery and roadmap.&lt;/strong&gt; Own product discovery — customer needs, market signal, and competitive dynamics — and develop the roadmap recommendations including business cases and prioritization. Present recommendations to TextUs&#39;s executive team for approval. Regularly present the roadmap to internal stakeholders and to customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product metrics and insight.&lt;/strong&gt; Regularly communicate insight into key product metrics across the organization — through Quarterly Business Reviews and other established mechanisms — connecting product performance to roadmap decisions and business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive and market intelligence.&lt;/strong&gt; Own product-level competitive positioning and intelligence, including the product and competitive view presented in Quarterly Business Reviews. Assess and address regulatory and technical constraints relevant to product decisions, and advocate for security, risk, and compliance in new feature definition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Briefs.&lt;/strong&gt; Author net-new Product Briefs end to end in collaboration with the Product Team. This includes problem definition, business rationale, customer evidence, key requirements and MVP definition, and the product-level constraints (limits, rules, and edge behavior) that determine what gets built. Briefs serve as the source of truth for the development process and must be complete enough to build against.&lt;/li&gt;
